Adds gate codes to LatePoint booking confirmations and summaries.

== Description ==

LatePoint Addon - Gate Codes enhances the LatePoint booking system by adding automatically generated gate codes to booking confirmations and summaries.

= Features =
* Automatically generates gate codes based on agent ID and booking week
* Displays gate codes in booking confirmations
* Shows gate codes in booking summaries
* Handles single and multiple bookings
* Mobile-friendly responsive design
* Print-friendly design

= Requirements =
* WordPress 5.0 or higher
* PHP 7.0 or higher
* LatePoint plugin must be installed and activated

== Installation ==

1. Upload the `latepoint-gate-codes` folder to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory
2. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress
3. No configuration is needed - gate codes will automatically appear in booking confirmations and summaries

== Frequently Asked Questions ==

= How are gate codes generated? =
Gate codes are generated using the agent ID and the week number of the booking date in the format #[agentID][agentID][weeknum].

= Will gate codes appear for all bookings? =
Gate codes will only appear for bookings with an 'approved' status.

= Can I customize the gate code format? =
The current version uses a fixed format. Future versions may include customization options.

= Is the gate code display optimized for different devices? =
Yes, the gate code display is fully responsive and will adapt to desktop, tablet, and mobile screens.

= Does the gate code work with print functionality? =
Yes, the addon includes specific print styling to ensure gate codes are clearly visible when booking information is printed.

